Subject: [PATCH] COMP: Restore Slicer_INSTALL_QTLOADABLEMODULES_LIB_DIR after
 UseSlicer.cmake

UseSlicer.cmake line 359 resets Slicer_INSTALL_QTLOADABLEMODULES_LIB_DIR to
"" when Slicer_QTLOADABLEMODULES_LIB_DIR is unset in standalone/system-install
builds. This caused loadable module .so files to install to bare lib/ instead
of lib/Slicer-5.8/qt-loadable-modules/, making them invisible to Slicer's
module discovery mechanism (SLICER_ADDITIONAL_MODULE_PATHS).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 Modules/Loadable/Terminologies/CMakeLists.txt | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Modules/Loadable/Terminologies/CMakeLists.txt b/Modules/Loadable/Terminologies/CMakeLists.txt
index 81f51b2673..acbdfbbd44 100644
--- a/Modules/Loadable/Terminologies/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/Modules/Loadable/Terminologies/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -19,6 +19,13 @@ if(NOT Slicer_INSTALL_QTLOADABLEMODULES_SHARE_DIR)
     "./share/Slicer-${Slicer_VERSION}/qt-loadable-modules")
 endif()
 
+# UseSlicer.cmake also resets Slicer_INSTALL_QTLOADABLEMODULES_LIB_DIR to empty
+# when Slicer_QTLOADABLEMODULES_LIB_DIR is unset (standalone build). Restore.
+if(NOT Slicer_INSTALL_QTLOADABLEMODULES_LIB_DIR)
+  set(Slicer_INSTALL_QTLOADABLEMODULES_LIB_DIR
+    "./lib/Slicer-${Slicer_VERSION}/qt-loadable-modules")
+endif()
+
 #-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 add_subdirectory(Logic)
 add_subdirectory(Widgets)
